Priestess Qa’tir Hindhart"
summerVersion = "Blessed greetings. I am Qa’tir, daughter of High Priestess Hindhart. Before I begin, know that I hold profound respect and admiration for your human kingdom. The manner in which your people have maintained sense of self in spite of sickness is a great inspiration—wiliting plagues are no trivial matter. If nothing else, I apologize for not extending my friendship and aid sooner.

Unfortunately, this letter is not merely an expression of well wishes, as it arrives at a period of troubling stagnation for my people. We Fae of Mosswyn have always been a scattered people, with many roaming the wood alone for decades at a time, but recently our numbers have been dwindling. I fear our morale has weakened in solitude, and so I set my sights on external biomes in search of cooperation and exchange. For all of our mana, we lack the livelihood to take advantage of our blessings, and are thus lacking in defense and prosperity. Rather than embodying the stable oak or the adaptable fox, my people have come to resemble that of the decomposers… festering, stagnant…decaying.

It saddens me to inform you that a handful of our citizens have perverted our faith in Moss. Nothing is certain, but I worry that they seek to infect not only the rest of our forest but the entire realm with their twisted sense of devotion. I dread the day that our faith is used as anything but a means of upholding order, honor, and interpersonal harmony. I fear that we need allies now, more than ever. I believe that ally is you."
