winterVersion = "Blessed greetings. I am Qa’tir, daughter of High Priestess Hindhart. Before I begin, know that I hold profound respect and admiration for your human kingdom. The manner in which your people have maintained sense of self in spite of sickness is a great inspiration—wiliting plagues are no trivial matter. If nothing else, I apologize for not extending my friendship and aid sooner.

Unfortunately, this letter is not merely an expression of well wishes, as it arrives at a period of troubling stagnation for my people. We Fae of Mosswyn have always been a scattered people, with many roaming the wood alone for decades at a time, but recently our numbers have been dwindling. I fear our morale has weakened in solitude, and so I set my sights on external biomes in search of cooperation and exchange. For all of our mana, we lack the livelihood to take advantage of our blessings, and are thus lacking in defense and prosperity. Rather than embodying the stable oak or the adaptable fox, my people have come to resemble that of the decomposers… festering, stagnant…decaying. But then, you have seen Withering. In this respect, I was deeply grieved to hear about your father—I will pray for his speedy recovery.

