springVersion = "The moment is nigh when you must choose a partner. Please forgive my urgency, but there is no time to waste.

In the spirit of companionship, I am sorry to admit that I have not revealed the extent of my knowledge. The fungi’s threat—that is, Briallon’s—is an intimate one; regrettably, the so called “Great Mycelian” is my ex-lover. I understand this puts you in an awkward situation, and trust that I wouldn’t share this information if it did not explain my unique insight into her plans. 

The Fungal Clan is, as you may already suspect, a cult. They do not wish to spread love, but rot. In fact, I wouldn’t be surprised if Briallon had something to do with the passing of your late father. He perished of the Withering, if I am not mistaken? Well, those symptoms look an awful like fungal mold. 

I am sorry if my words are upsetting, but they are imperative. While Mosswyn remains unaffected by the physical plagues of humans, we are not immune to spiritual and psychological rot. The cult has festered like a fungus in unsanitary areas, decomposing and destroying the minds of all whom take part. Only when united can our kingdoms put a stop to this. I look forward to hearing your decision regarding my proposal. "
